TY  - JOUR
T1  - The Pasinetti Paradox in a two-class monetary growth model
AU  - Ramanathan, R.
JO  - Journal of Monetary Economics
VL  - 2
IS  - 3
SP  - 389
EP  - 397
PY  - 1976
DA  - 1976/07/01/
SN  - 0304-3932
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-3932(76)90025-8
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304393276900258
AB  - The paper extends the well-known, two-class model of economic growth by incorporating a monetary sector. Thus capitalists and workers not only save different proportions of their incomes and earn dividend income on capital assets but also have different demands for money. This is turn alters the portfolio composition in a dissimilar way. It is shown that when a monetary sector is added, the condition for the so called Pasinetti Paradox is empirically more plausible. The paper also examines the stability of the model.
ER  - 

